<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 11:25PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Pondera
County through MIDNIGHT MDT...
At 1124 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Valier, or 12 miles northwest of Conrad, moving southwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
